16 (7) Investigating whether businesses are adhering to their obligations, including
17 those undertaken as part of the Race to the Top scoring system, and
18 recommending corrective action or discipline if they fail to do so, which may
19 include a suspension or revocation of licenses.
20 "Article 3.
21 "Registration and Licensure.
22 "§ 18D-300. Registration with the Department.
23 (a) Each application or renewal application for an annual registration to operate a
24 cannabis establishment shall be submitted to the Department. A renewal application may be
25 submitted up to 90 days prior to the expiration of the cannabis establishment's registration.
26 (b) The Department shall begin accepting and processing applications to operate cannabis
27 establishments from historically impacted applicants one year after the effective date of this
28 Chapter.
29 (c) The Department may begin accepting and processing applications to operate cannabis
30 establishments from applicants other than historically impacted applicants no earlier than one
31 year and 180 days after the effective date of this Chapter.
32 (d) Upon receiving an application or renewal application for a cannabis establishment,
33 the Department shall immediately forward a copy of each application and half of the registration
34 application fee to the local regulatory authority for the locality in which the applicant desires to
35 operate the cannabis establishment, unless the locality has not designated a local regulatory
36 authority.
37 (e) Within 120 days after receiving an application or renewal application, the Department
38 shall issue an annual registration or a conditional registration to the applicant, unless the
39 Department finds the applicant is not in compliance with rules enacted by the Department or the
40 Department is notified by the relevant locality that the applicant is not in compliance with
41 ordinances and regulations in effect at the time of application.
42 (f) Applicants may apply for conditional approval if they have not purchased or leased
43 the property where their cannabis establishment would be located. If the applicant is otherwise
44 qualified, the Department shall provide conditional approval. Once the applicant provides the
45 Department with a completed, supplemental application that includes the premises, the
46 Department shall forward the information to the local regulatory authority and approve or reject
47 the final application within 45 days from the date of submission.
48 (g) Upon denial of an application, the Department shall notify the applicant in writing of
49 the specific reason for its denial.
50 (h) Cannabis establishments, and the books and records maintained and created by
51 cannabis establishments, are subject to inspection by the Department.
