14 "§ 18D-409. Lawful operation of cannabis-related facilities.
15 (a) Notwithstanding any other provision of law, engaging in any activities involving
16 cannabis, cannabis accessories, or cannabis products, if the person conducting the activities has
17 obtained a current, valid registration to operate a cannabis establishment or is acting in his or her
18 capacity as an owner, employee, or agent of a registered cannabis establishment and the activities
19 are within the scope of activities allowed by the Department for that type of cannabis
20 establishment, is not unlawful and shall not be an offense under State law or be a basis for seizure
21 or forfeiture of assets under State law.
22 (b) Nothing in this section prevents the imposition of penalties for violating this Chapter
23 or rules adopted by the Department or localities pursuant to this Chapter.
24 "§ 18D-410. Verifying the age of cannabis consumers.
25 (a) A cannabis establishment or an agent or staffer of a cannabis establishment may not
26 sell, deliver, distribute, give, transfer, or otherwise furnish cannabis to a person under the age of
27 21.
28 (b) Except as otherwise provided in this section, in a prosecution for selling, transferring,
29 delivering, distributing, giving, or otherwise furnishing cannabis, cannabis products, or cannabis
30 accessories to any person who is under 21 years of age, it is a complete defense if both of the
31 following requirements are met:
32 (1) The person who sold, gave, or otherwise furnished cannabis, cannabis
33 products, or cannabis accessories was a retail cannabis store or on-site
34 consumption establishment or was acting in his or her capacity as an owner,
35 employee, or agent of a retail cannabis store or on-site consumption
36 establishment at the time the cannabis, cannabis products, or cannabis
37 accessories were sold, given, or otherwise furnished to the person.
38 (2) Before selling, giving, or otherwise furnishing cannabis, cannabis products,
39 or cannabis accessories to a person who is under 21 years of age, the person
40 who sold, gave, or otherwise furnished the cannabis or cannabis accessories,
41 or a staffer or agent of the retail cannabis store, was shown a document that
42 appeared to be issued by an agency of a federal, state, tribal, or foreign
43 sovereign government and that indicated that the person to whom the cannabis
44 or cannabis accessories were sold, given, or otherwise furnished was 21 years
45 of age or older at the time the cannabis or cannabis accessories were sold,
46 given, or otherwise furnished to the person.
47 (c) Subsection (b) of this section does not apply if both of the following requirements are
48 met:
49 (1) The document that was shown to the person who sold, gave, or otherwise
50 furnished the cannabis, cannabis products, or cannabis accessories was
51 counterfeit, forged, altered, or issued to a person other than the person to
