10 PART II. AUTOMATIC EXPUNCTION OF MARIJUANA OFFENSES
11 SECTION 2.1. Article 5 of Chapter 15A of the General Statutes is amended by
12 adding a new section to read:
13 "§ 15A-145.8B. Automatic expunction of certain marijuana offenses.
14 (a) If a person was charged with an offense involving marijuana or hashish that is legal
15 under Chapter 18D of the General Statutes, and such person was convicted, such conviction shall
16 be ordered to be automatically expunged no later than July 1, 2028, in the manner set forth in
17 this section.
18 (b) The Administrative Office of the Courts shall determine which offenses meet the
19 criteria for expunction set forth in subsection (a) of this section. Upon completing the
20 determination required under this subsection, the Administrative Office of the Courts shall
21 provide an electronic list of the offenses to the clerk of each superior court. Upon receipt of the
22 electronic list required under this subsection, the clerk of each superior court shall prepare an
23 order of expungement for each case that meets the criteria set forth in subsection (a) of this section
24 and was finalized in his or her court. Upon completion of the order of expungement, the court
25 shall order the expunction. Upon order of expungement, the clerk shall forward the petition to
26 the Administrative Office of the Courts.
27 (c) No person as to whom such an order has been entered under this section shall be held
28 thereafter under any provision of any law to be guilty of perjury, or to be guilty of otherwise
29 giving a false statement or response to any inquiry made for any purpose, by reason of the
30 person's failure to recite or acknowledge any expunged entries concerning apprehension, charge,
31 or trial.
32 (d) The court shall also order that the conviction ordered expunged under this section be
33 expunged from the records of the court and direct all law enforcement agencies bearing record
34 of the same to expunge their records of the conviction. The clerk shall notify State and local
35 agencies of the court's order as provided in G.S. 15A-150.
36 (e) Any other applicable State or local government agency shall expunge from its records
37 entries made as a result of the conviction ordered expunged under this section. The agency shall
38 also reverse any administrative actions taken against a person whose record is expunged under
39 this section as a result of the charges or convictions expunged. This subsection shall not apply to
40 the Department of Justice for DNA records and samples stored in the State DNA Database and
41 the State DNA Databank."
42 SECTION 2.2. The Administrative Office of the Courts shall provide the list
43 required under G.S. 15A-145.8B(b), as enacted by this Part, by October 1, 2027.
44 SECTION 2.3. This Part becomes effective January 1, 2026.
45
